---
title: Spiced Chicken Burrito Bowls with Guacamole & Mango-Bell Pepper Relish
description: Get ready to relish this relish! Bell pepper and mango are sautéed with sugar until tender and jammy, then mixed with onion, lime juice, and olive oil for a tangy topper. The fruity garnish is perfectly paired with fluffy jasmine rice, Mexican-spiced pork, and creamy guacamole. Breezy burrito bowls with a tropical twist? Ahh… welcome to (weeknight) paradise.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/62a0a406227ef5271c006294-d38dcf81.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/spiced-chicken-burrito-bowls-62a0a406227ef5271c006294-5260c846.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spiced-chicken-burrito-bowls-62a0a406227ef5271c006294
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Latin
nutrition:
  calories: 700 kcal
  fat: 24 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 90 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 31 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 590 mg
servings: 2
---

In a small #pot, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water (2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook, covered, until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Halve, core, and finely dice @bell pepper{1}. Drain @mango{4%ounce}, reserving juice. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(finely diced). Mince some of the diced onion until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings); set aside for step 5. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add mango and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly charred, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Add 1/4 cup water and @sugar{1/2%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4 servings); cook until liquid has reduced and mostly evaporated, ~{30%seconds}.

Turn off heat; transfer mango mixture to a #medium bowl. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium high-heat. Add diced onion and season with salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @chicken breast strips{10%ounce}, @Mexican spice blend{1%tablespoon}, salt (we used 1/2 tsp; 1 tsp for 4 servings), and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir in reserved mango juice and cook until thickened, ~{30%seconds}. Remove from heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> Rinse shrimp under cold water. Pat shrimp or chicken dry with paper towels. Swap in shrimp or chicken for pork; cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, 3-4 minutes for shrimp or 4-6 minutes for chicken. Cook through the rest of this step as instructed.

Add minced onion, juice from one @lime{1}(juiced) (juice from 1 1/2 limes for 4 servings; taste and add more if desired), and a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} to bowl with the mango mixture; stir to combine. Taste and season generously with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork; stir in lime zest. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls. Top with pork, relish, and @guacamole{4%tablespoon} in separate sections. Serve.